similar to aug_26, but with a soliton-like
connectivity wave propagating with the body
of the network...

conceptually you can think about the important
part of matrices involved in this example as
2*N - the rest is just for decorative purposes
or future additions...

This is the important part of the program:

  (outputs[0]).matrix[1][1] = 1.0;
  (outputs[1]).matrix[1][1] = -1.0;
  (outputs[1]).matrix[1][3] = 1.0;
  (outputs[3]).matrix[1][3] = -1.0;
  (outputs[3]).matrix[1][5] = 1.0;
  (outputs[5]).matrix[1][5] = -1.0;
  (outputs[5]).matrix[1][7] = 1.0;
  (outputs[7]).matrix[1][7] = -1.0;
  (outputs[7]).matrix[1][9] = 1.0;
  (outputs[9]).matrix[1][9] = -1.0;
  (outputs[9]).matrix[1][1] = 1.0;

